  <histories>
    <history>
      <header>The first steps of DNT</header>
      <text>
      Do Not Touch was originally a prototype conceived by Flat Pixel's co-founders and Nickelodeon in late 2017.
      With the ARKit technology and a lot of creativity this little prototype evolved to its release on the App Store in March 2018.
      </text>
    </history>
    <history>
      <header>.. leading to its release </header>
      <text>
      In the first version of DNT, the concept was really simple : just place the button on a flat surface and press it, then .. something happens.
      The risk paid off and the Kids loved it! Do Not Touch 1.0 even won Flat Pixel its first Clio Entertainment Award for the category Virtual/Augmented Reality in 2018.
      </text>
    </history>
    <history>
      <header>Do Not Touch 2.0</header>
      <text>
      A year later, Do Not Touch got an upgrade.
      A collection system and a simple economy were added that rewarded users with slime points that they could spend to unlock new mini-games and wacky button skins.
      A second Clio Entertainment in Virtual/Augmented Reality soon followed in 2019!
      </text>
    </history>
  </histories>

